text_1:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3: 
 1.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
 2.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
 3.USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
 4.The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
text_2:
This happened on the day December 3rd: 
 Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.

 Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
text_2:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
 2.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
 3.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 4.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 5.Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
 6.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.

French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.

text_1:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3: 
 1.USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
 2.Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
 3.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
 4.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.

This happened on the day December 3rd: 
 The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
text_2:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3: 
 1.French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
 2.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 3.Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
 4.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.

 1.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 2.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
 3.Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
 4.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 5.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 6.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.

text_1:

 4.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.

Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
text_2:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
 2.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
 3.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 4.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 5.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
 6.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.

 2.Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
 3.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 4.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.

 3.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 4.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.

This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.

USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.

 2.French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
 3.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 4.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 5.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
 6.Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.

Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.

 1.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 2.Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
 3.USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
 4.French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
 5.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
 6.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.

Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
text_2:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
 2.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
 3.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 4.Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
 5.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
 6.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.

 2.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
 3.Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
 4.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 5.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 6.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.

 1.Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
 2.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 3.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 4.French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
text_2:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
 2.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 3.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 4.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 5.Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
 6.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.

 2.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
 3.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 4.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 5.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
 6.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.

 2.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 3.Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
 4.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
 5.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 6.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.

 French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.

 2.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
 3.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 4.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 5.Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
 6.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.

 1.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
 2.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 3.Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
 4.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
 5.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 6.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
text_2:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 2.Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
 3.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 4.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 5.USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
 6.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.

 5.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
 6.Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.

Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.

text_1:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
 2.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
 3.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 4.French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
 5.Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
 6.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
